widgets_values:
Batch prompts on .txt file

You can create a batch of prompts, save it on a .txt file and use that file for automatic image generation.

The .txt file must be formatted as follow (as example with just 2 prompts):


positive: a girl is walking through street, raincoat, yellow umbrella

negative: (leave empty)

-------

positive:museum, people are looking paintings, abstract

negative: (leave empty)

-------


The file has to be saved in the following folder:

/custom_nodes/ComfyUI-Inspire-Pack/prompts/example/

The photograph is a stunning high-resolution image that captures the serene beauty of a sunset by the harbor. The main focus of the image is an elderly man with a full, thick, and well-groomed white beard and mustache. His beard is long, reaching down to his chest, and is neatly combed, giving him a wise and distinguished appearance. His mustache is equally impressive, curling up at the ends and framing his mouth perfectly.

The man is dressed in a simple yet practical outfit, consisting of a blue button-down shirt, dark-wash jeans, and a pair of brown leather boots. He is sitting on a weathered wooden bench, with his hands resting on his knees and his gaze fixed on the horizon. The bench appears to be old and well-used, with chipped paint and worn-down wood, adding to the overall rustic charm of the scene.

In the background, the harbor is bustling with activity, with boats of various sizes and shapes moored to the docks. The water is a deep shade of blue, reflecting the fiery hues of the setting sun. In the distance, the sun is slowly sinking below the horizon, casting a warm orange glow over the entire scene. The sky is a riot of colors, with shades of pink, purple, and blue blending seamlessly into one another.

Despite the activity in the background, the man in the photograph appears to be lost in thought, oblivious to the world around him. His expression is calm and contemplative, with a hint of a smile playing on his lips. The overall mood of the photograph is one of peace and tranquility, with the beauty of the sunset and the serene expression of the man creating a sense of harmony and balance.

nodes.title: Unnamed
widgets_values:
---Img2img module---

For best results I suggest to use the Florence-2-large-PromptGen-v1.5 model, with fp32 precision.
Use the "img2img Denoise" selector (range 0.30 - 0.90) to choose the strength of the new image over the original input, higher values will modify more the final output making it closer to the prompt (above 0.85 the image may be completely different).  I suggest to stay between 0.4 and 0.6.

--Sharpen settings--

For portraits I suggest to use the following settings:

-Noise_radius: 7
-Preserve_edges: 0.60
-Sharpen: 3.0
-Ratio: 0.4

For other kind of image you could try with higher Sharpen values (6-7).

nodes.title: Unnamed
widgets_values:
--LUT Module--

LUT are a kind of "filter" that allows you to modify your image colors, contrast saturation and tones, giving them an "analogic-film" look. You can find and download free LUT from many websites. I use mainly this one:

https://www.freepresets.com/product-category/free-luts-color-lookup-table/film-free-luts-color-lookup-table/

LUT files must be downloaded in the following folder: ../ComfyUI/custom_nodes/ComfyUI_essentials/luts/

Some of the most used analogic film were the following:
-Fuji Provia medium color-saturation and contrast. Wide range of applications, such as product, landscape, nature and fashion photography as well as portraiture.
-FUji Astia smooth and natural skin tone reproduction from the highlights to the shadows and exceptionally fine grain. Ideally suited for fashion photography and portraiture.
-Kodak Portra daylight-balanced professional color negative films originally introduced in 1998 made mainly for portrait and wedding applications.
-Fuji Velvia superb granularity, and world-class levels of image color-saturation and vibrancy. Vivid color reproduction and excellent image quality.
-Agfa Ultra 100
-Kodakcrome

nodes.title: Image Compare:  Flux original vs Faceswapped one
Unnamed
widgets_values:
--Suggested Settings for portraits--

  1. Latent Upscale (rng 1.0 - 2.0): 1.20 - 1.50
    Best results around 1.25
  2. Flux guidance (rng 0.0 - 5.0): 3.00- 3.50
    Best results around original image Guidance
  3. Denoise (rng 0.45 - 0.90): 0.55 - 0.60
    High values may change the image
  4. Speed-Accuracy (rng 1.0 - 2.0): 0.50 - 0.75
    Latent injection steps: more = more details
  5. Noise Strength (rng 0.10 - 0.60): 0.30 - 0.40
    High noise strength will overcook images
  6. Rough-Smooth (rng 0.40 - 0.80): 0.60 - 0.70
    For portrait is better to stay above 0.60
